# Core Standards

- Make the smallest correct change; no unrelated refactors.
- Match existing naming, imports, and patterns in the surrounding file.
- Prefer editing existing modules over creating new ones unless splitting a god file.
- Use Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`).
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, service account keys, API keys).
- Run `npm run format` before committing; frontend lint via `npm run lint`.
- See [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) for architecture rules and file-size targets.
